<font color="#FF0000">BLACK VETERANS</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct 18 22:46:25 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I carried machine gun ammo for TJ (Thomas Johnson) a black soldier from Chicago.  We went to Vung Tau together on a three day pass.  We had a great time.  He was (is) a helluva man.  I admired him.  He saved my life once.  Black/white is a non issue for me.  It never existed for me in Cu Chi, South Vietnam or since.<br><br>
There is something about being a soldier that brings out the best in men and women.  Isn't that nice.  There's a lot of wisdom and tolerance that comes from veterans of all wars.<br>
And it is wisdom.<br><br>
Paul
